@startuml
start

:Citizen submits enquiry or feedback via website, phone, chat/mobile, or email;
:Create Case with channel origin, record type, service category, and attachments;
:Verify citizen by phone or email against external MDM;

if (Citizen verified?) then (Yes)
  :Link or update Contact;
else (No)
  :Flag for manual verification and continue with restricted handling;
endif

:Route through Omni-Channel using expertise, language, workload, and availability;
:Agent reviews Case in Service Console;

if (Case type?) then (Enquiry)
  :Search Knowledge for existing solution;
  if (Existing solution available?) then (Yes)
    :Provide approved solution to citizen;
  else (No)
    :Develop resolution and submit Knowledge draft;
  endif
  if (Complex enquiry?) then (Yes)
    :Escalate to Supervisor;
  endif
  :Perform follow-up until citizen confirms resolution;
else (Feedback)
  :Analyze satisfaction level, service category, and improvement area;
  if (Citizen response required?) then (Yes)
    :Respond to citizen;
  endif
  :Include in internal reporting and trend analysis;
  :Supervisor evaluates handling outcome and agent performance;
endif

:Close Case with resolution summary, confirmation, and audit trail;
:Branch Admin monitors dashboards by division, channel, SLA, and agent;

stop
@enduml
